1. HTTP Protocol â€“ Basics
    a) HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol)
        * Text-based client-server protocol for the Internet
        * For transferring Web resources (HTML files, images, styles, etc.)
        * Request-response based, relies on URLs (like https://softuni.org)
        * Stateless
    b) front-end and back-end
        * front-end and back-end separate the modern apps into client-side and server-side components
        * front-end - the client-side component. Implements the user interface
        * back-end - the server-side component. Provides data storage and processing
        * HTTP connects front-end and back-end

2. HTML forms
    * The "action" attribute defines where to submit the form data
        <form action = "home.html">
            <input type = "submit" value = "Go" />
        </form>
    * forms can specify the HTTP method for sending the form data
        <form method = "get">     <---"post"
            Name: <input type = "text" name = "name">
            <br> </br>
            <input type = "submit" value = "Go">
        </form>

3. HTTP response status codes.
    * 200 - OK
    * 201 - created
    * 204 - no content
    * 301/302 - moved
    * 400 - bad request
    * 401/403 - unauthorized
    * 404 - not found
    * 409 - conflict
    * 500/503 - server error

4. URL
    * https://mysite.com:8080/demo/index.php?id=27&lang=en#lectures
